<s> If I understood you correctly, this means: 1. Parameters are a syntactic construct in RFC 2396 which allows extensions to path segments of hierarchical uris.  </s>
<s> There is no predefined semantics to segment parameters.  </s>
<s> 2. Parameters are opaque to the "receiver" of an uri.  </s>
<s> For comparision, and especially for resolving uris, parameters are treated as part of the path segment.  </s>
<s> 3. An authority for the uri, what you call "service", is free to use parameters however it likes in matching uris to resources and vice versa.  </s>
<s> (follows from opacity)  </s>
<s> 4. Queries are different from parameters as: - queries on base uris do not take part in resolving references when the reference has a non-empty path.  </s>
<s> - queries can be setup by a client (HTML forms)  </s>
